Every year, design evolves — and 2026 is all about emotion, texture and quiet drama. Here are the eight trends shaping the weddings we're designing right now.

## 1. Sculptural Florals

Flowers are becoming architecture. Think suspended installations, floral arches that frame the couple, and single-variety monochrome moments that feel like art.

## 2. Candlelit Maximalism

Hundreds of tapers, warm amber glow and layered tablescapes. Restraint is out; intentional abundance is in.

## 3. Earthy Luxe Palettes

Terracotta, olive, mushroom and gold — grounded tones that feel timeless in photographs and never date.

## 4. Personalised Escort Moments

Custom stationery, wax seals and hand-calligraphed details that make every guest feel individually welcomed.

## 5. Statement Ceiling Design

The most underused canvas at any wedding is above your head. Draped fabric, hanging greenery and chandelier clusters transform a room instantly.

## 6. Mixed Seating

Long banquet tables meeting intimate rounds — a layout that feels collected, warm and anything but corporate.

## 7. Après-Ceremony Lounges

Curated lounge vignettes give guests a place to gather, sink in and celebrate between the formal moments.

## 8. Sustainable Design

Reusable structures, potted florals guests take home, and local sourcing — beauty with a conscience.

